The 13C chemical shift was referenced to the methyl signal of hexamethyl benzene
resonating at 19.2 ppm which gives chemical shift relative to DSS (2, 2-
dimethylsilapentane-5-sulfonic acid) (Morcombe and Zilm, 2003).
The 15N chemical shift reference was computed from the ratios of resonance
frequencies in the IUPAC recommendations.
